description: While the whole world sailed east on the path to find China, Columbus believed it could be reached in two weeks… by sailing west!

title: The Prodigal Son
description: The Prodigal Son is a parable of a wayward son reunited with his father and family after having squandered all his inheritance through wasteful and idolatrous living.

title: Esther
description: Queen Esther faces the deadly dilemma of risking her life to save her countrymen.  Her courage and wisdom helps turn a tragedy into a victory.

title: Daniel
description: Daniel’s enemies plan a trap to have him thrown in the lions’ den. But Daniel survives and proves that God still rules over the affairs of men.

title: Elisha
description: As a fiery chariot from heaven took away Elijah, his mantle fell upon his frightened protégé, Elisha. From then on, Elisha would be God’s mouthpiece.

title: David and Goliath
description: David, a young shepherd boy, seems an unlikely candidate to save his nation from ruin. But when Goliath defies Israel and blasphemes God, young David leaps into action.

title: Moses
description: Watch God’s hand as a tiny baby, found in the bulrushes by an Egyptian princess, is reared to be a powerful Egyptian ruler and deliver Israel.

title: Solomon
description: It was his first major test as king. The dilemma was two mothers both laying claim to one baby. Lives depended on Solomon’s excruciating decision.

title: Samuel the Boy Prophet
description: In keeping her vow, Hannah dedicates her child to God. From his days as a young boy serving Eli to guiding the ancient Israelites, Samuel the prophet stands as an inspiring exam

title: Ruth
description: When Naomi and her two daughters-in-law are left as widows, Naomi begs them to care for themselves by returning to their own people. One agrees—but Ruth declares she will never

title: Joseph's Reunion
description: The drought left Canaan bare of crops, yet Egypt had vast storehouses of food. Jacob sent ten of his sons to Pharaoh to buy provisions. They never imagined that there they would

title: Joseph in Egypt
description: Joseph is sold into slavery by his jealous brothers and taken to Egypt. Because of his integrity and insight he is given power in Pharaoh’s court.

title: Abraham and Isaac
description: When God commands Abraham to offer Isaac as a sacrifice to Him, Abraham must make the most difficult decision of his life and be tested in his trust and faith in God.

title: The Ministry of Paul
description: Paul’s powerful preaching and example bring conversion as persecution is answered, again and again, with the gospel of love.

title: Treasures in Heaven
description: Treasures in Heaven is a story of contrast between two men who seek to follow Jesus and what they are willing to give up to receive salvation.

title: Lord, I Believe
description: Lord, I Believe is a collection of three stories where Jesus teaches His disciples the power of faith. Matthew 8–10, 17, 19, 21; Mark 9, 11; and Luke 7, 18

title: Saul of Tarsus
description: Saul is changed forever when the resurrected Lord appears to him on the Road to Damascus. Saul becomes reborn as Paul, one of the greatest missionaries and apostles for Jesus.

title: The Lord's Prayer
description: Jesus taught His disciples the power of prayer through  example. After Jesus' resurrection, Peter is cast into prison. Through faith and prayer, Peter’s chains are broken.

title: The Greatest is the Least
description: In the years following Jesus' resurrection, the disciples learn to practice His teachings.

title: Worthy is the Lamb
description: Witness the fulfillment of ancient prophecies. See Jesus in the Garden of Gethsemane. Rejoice in the knowledge that His death and resurrection provides us a way back to Him.

title: The Messiah Comes
description: In Jesus' final days, His disciples struggle to understand. Following His death, He visits them and they finally realize: Jesus delivers all from the bondage of sin and death.

title: Signs of the Times
description: Jesus uses the parables of the King’s Wedding Feast and the Thief in the Night to teach His disciples and us to repent and be prepared for the day He comes again.

title: The Kingdom of Heaven
description: The Kingdom of Heaven is a series of parables. As Jesus teaches the people each parable, some begin to understand what the “Kingdom of Heaven” is like.

title: Lazarus Lives
description: Lazarus Lives gives assurance that Jesus has all power over death and offers the promise of eternal life to all who believe in Him.

title: John the Baptist
description: John the Baptist is a story of courage and conviction seen through the life of one of God’s greatest prophets who gave everything to prepare the way for the Lord.

title: The Righteous Judge
description: The Righteous Judge recreates the events that surround Jesus in teaching the principles of love, forgiveness and righteous judgment.  John 7–9.

title: The Parables of Jesus
description: The parables of Jesus reinforce important principles. These truths help us focus on our faith in God and His power to help us live our lives in accordance with His teachings.

title: The Lost is Found
description: Those who recognize their sins rejoice that Jesus would help anyone so lost. See how Jesus extends His mercy to each sinner and lovingly brings them back to the fold.

title: The Good Samaritan
description: The Good Samaritan tells the parable of the robbers, the Rabbi, the Levite and the wounded traveler. Jesus teaches us to love and serve one another no matter how we differ.

title: Bread from Heaven
description: Jesus offers will satisfy one’s hunger forever. This delightful story of the feeding of the 5,000 challenges us to consider afresh the One who is the Bread of Life.

title: The Miracles of Jesus
description: See a panorama of Jesus’ most touching miracles. Healing the sick, raising Jairus’ dead daughter, and calming the storm are attributed to the principle of faith.

title: Built Upon the Rock
description: Jesus affirms the eternal ideals taught in the Sermon on the Mount. Important ideals of preparedness are emphasized through the parable of the House Built on the Rock.

title: Jesus, The Son of God
description: This story begins with Jesus’ early years and follows with His triumph over Satan's Temptations, marking the beginning of His ministry.

title: He is Risen
description: See the story of the greatest miracle of all, the resurrection and ascension of Jesus, teaching of the atonement and providing hope to Christians around the world.

title: The King is Born
description: See the timeless story of the birth of Jesus come to life, from Gabriel appearing to Mary to His birth in the stable. Matthew 1–2, 13; and Luke 1–2.
